+# Task 2: Friend Management Extension
+
+## Overview
+This extends the baseline CLI login/registration system (Task 1) with friend management functionality, including adding, removing, listing friends, and entering chat mode.
+
+## New Features
+
+### Friend Management Menu
+After successful login, users see a friend management menu:
+- `[A] Add Friend` - Add a new friend
+- `[R] Remove Friend` - Remove an existing friend
+- `[L] List Friends` - Display all friends with status
+- `[C] Choose Friend` - Enter chat mode with a friend
+- `[Q] Logout` - Return to main menu
+
+### Friend Persistence
+- Friends are stored in `data/friends_<username>.json`
+- Format: JSON array of `{"user": "string", "status": "online|offline"}`
+- Default status: `offline`
+- Data persists across application restarts
+
+### Chat Mode
+- Select `[C]` and enter friend ID (0-based index)
+- Displays header: `--- Chat with <friend> ---`
+- Type `/back` to return to friend menu
+
+### Selftest
+- Command: `./bin/chat_app --selftest friend-menu`
+- Output: Compact JSON `{"user": "...", "friends": [...]}`
+- Matches persisted data from `data/friends_<username>.json`
+- Exits with code 0
+
+## Building and Running
+
+### Build
+```bash
+make task2
+```
+
+### Run Application
+```bash
+./bin/chat_app
+```
+
+### Run Selftest
+```bash
+./bin/chat_app --selftest friend-menu
+```
+
+### Verify Implementation
+```bash
+./verify_task2.sh
+```
+
+## Usage Examples
+
+### Complete Workflow
+```
+$ ./bin/chat_app
